#compdef capact
# ============================================================================
# _capact — zsh completion for **capact** — capactio/capact, the
#            **Collective Capability Manager** — a Kubernetes-native
#            declarative orchestration platform built around the
#            **Open Capability Format (OCF)** specification.  Operators
#            author typed `Interface` definitions ("what capability is
#            needed" — e.g. "I need a managed Postgres database"), and
#            the platform composes typed `Implementation` workflows
#            from a pluggable Hub that turns those abstract Interfaces
#            into concrete provisioning workflows (Helm chart install,
#            Terraform apply, AWS RDS create, GCP Cloud SQL create,
#            Crossplane composition, ArgoCD Application sync,
#            external GitLab/GitHub Actions trigger).  All driven by
#            **typed GraphQL APIs** generated via the canonical Go
#            GraphQL library **99designs/gqlgen** — the dominant
#            schema-first Go GraphQL server.  Go=178 leader bump
#            continuing Axis 123 (GraphQL / Facebook RFC GraphQL
#            specification + GraphQL HTTP transport + GraphQL
#            Subscriptions) at 2/0/0.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/capactio/capact
#   Maintainer : Capact.io (now archived as Project Capact at the
#                 SUSE / Rancher organization; original commercial
#                 sponsor SUSE-incubated CNCF Sandbox candidate;
#                 lead authors: Pawel Kosiec, Pawel Strzelewicz,
#                 Lukasz Iwaszkiewicz, Mateusz Szostok plus 40+
#                 contributors from SUSE / Rancher Labs)
#   License    : Apache-2.0
#   Stars      : 79
#   Language   : Go  (spf13/cobra for the CLI surface +
#                 99designs/gqlgen v0.13.0 for the GraphQL server-
#                 side codegen + the typed `gateway` GraphQL
#                 federated supergraph that exposes the
#                 `local-hub` + `public-hub` + `action` +
#                 `engine` + `policy` subgraphs as one unified
#                 schema + Argo Workflows for the underlying
#                 Kubernetes workflow engine + Helm 3 for chart
#                 installations + k3d for the bundled local
#                 cluster)
#   Binary     : capact  (defined via `var Name = "capact"` in
